comm_cricinfo: first ball duck for Gayle, Umesh has struck and the crowd is making plenty of noise, I don't know why! Movement off the pitch for Umesh as he pitches it on good length around middle, Gayle looks to defend it with soft hands but the ball moves away and a leading edge lobs like a balloon to short cover
comm_cricbuzz: 0.1    U Yadav to Gayle, out Caught by Gambhir!! Oh dear! Back-to-back ducks for Gayle, he is OUT first ball in his 100th IPL match. On a good length and a hint of shape back into the left-hander, Gayle was looking to work it towards the on-side. Did the ball stop on him, he closed the bat face early, the leading edge popped in the air and Gambhir raced in from cover to gobble it up. Worst possible start for RCB as Gayle walks away. Gayle c Gambhir b U Yadav 0(1)

comm_cricbuzz: 6.4    Aniket Choudhary to de Grandhomme, no run, he can't touch one. Back of length, probably a cutter, bounces spongily and over de Grandhomme's bat as he cuts. Three in a row

shortText: Choudhary to de Grandhomme, no run
comm_cricinfo: offcutter, back of a length outside off, cuts it this time, but straight to backward point
comm_cricbuzz: 6.5    Aniket Choudhary to de Grandhomme, no run, finally connects but cuts it straight to backward point

shortText: Choudhary to de Grandhomme, no run
comm_cricinfo: beats him again. This would've been wide if Grandhomme had stayed back. As it turned out, he gave it the charge and looked to slash through the off side, only to be beaten by angle
comm_cricbuzz: 6.6    Aniket Choudhary to de Grandhomme, no run, a wicket maiden. Can this match get any more bizarre? de Grandhomme gives him the charge, flashes away from the body and misses again

comm_cricinfo: good length at off stump. Doesn't hit it for six. Incredible. Instead, goes forward, dabs it into the off side and brings up his fifty
comm_cricbuzz: 7.1    Negi to Chris Lynn, 1 run, slow on off, Lynn pats it with the turn into the off-side to bring up his half-century. It's come off 21 balls, at a snail's pace

comm_cricinfo: tossed up at off stump, driven firmly to long-off, who was slightly wide
comm_cricbuzz: 7.2    Negi to de Grandhomme, 1 run, looped up on off, de Grandhomme drives it powerfully down to long-off

comm_cricinfo: and that's the end. Arm ball doesn't rise from back of a length, skids through and into middle-n-leg as Lynn is tall while attempting to pull this
comm_cricbuzz: 7.3    Negi to Chris Lynn, out Bowled!! Got him. That's scooted through to shatter the stumps as Lynn lines up a pull. Darted in short, Lynn expects the ball to get up so he can pummel it into the stands. Not quite. RCB can chew the leftovers of their carcass. Chris Lynn b Negi 50(22) [4s-5 6s-4]

wkt_text: C de Grandhomme st †Jadhav b Negi 31 (29m 28b 1x4 2x6) SR: 110.71
comm_cricinfo: oh good ball. Very good ball. Good length, drifting in at off stump, but also dipping fast. He's down the pitch and realises soon he won't get bat on this. Offers a flick across the line anyway, but it spins past him and the keeper makes no mistake
comm_cricbuzz: 13.2    Negi to de Grandhomme, out Stumped!! Oh beautifully bowled. That's wonderful deception in flight. He slows it down, gives it some air to lure de Grandhomme out of his crease and then gets it to dip and turn past him. de Grandhomme runs past the ball. Lovely. Easy stumping for Jadhav. de Grandhomme st Kedar Jadhav b Negi 31(28) [4s-1 6s-2]

wkt_text: G Gambhir c Negi b Chahal 14 (26m 16b 0x4 0x6) SR: 87.50
comm_cricinfo: another annoying delay if you're a KKR fan. This is tossed up generously, wide outside off stump. He goes for the full blooded cover drive, but he has hit it in the air. Straight to extra cover
comm_cricbuzz: 14.1    Chahal to Gambhir, out Caught by Negi!! Another wicket. It's brought a smile on a couple of faces for RCB. Chahal drifts this wide of off, Gambhir chases it for the drive wanting to smash it through the covers but because it's so wide, he gets it close to the bottom of the bat which spoils his timing. Skews it to short cover. Gambhir c Negi b Chahal 14(16)
